An Arubian is a person born and bred (or naturalised) on the island of Aruba.

Aruba is an island in the caribbean. 

It forms part of what is considered to the dutch caribbean (6 islands formerly colonized by the Dutch e.g. Aruba, Boniare, Curacao, Saba, St. Eustatius and St. Martin). 

Geographically, Aruba is located in front of the coast of South America (namely Venezuela).